        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/261">Chuonradus</persName> ipsius dispensatione Romanorum
                            [<rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs>] augustus. Quia nullus extra
                        aecclesiam salvus potest fieri, consequens est, ut unusquisque fidelis
                        laborans in agro dei sine intermissione incumbat incremento ecclesiastice
                        rei. Certum est enim, quia, sicut exaltatur mater omnium viventium, ita
                        crescit merces omnium sibi servientium. Quapropter universorum eiusdem
                        fidelium tam presencium quam futurorum noverit caritas, quod nos
                        ecclesiasticis profectibus incumbentes ac dilectissime nostre <persName
                            key="#Queen" ref="#people/262">Gisle</persName> imperatricis seu
                        carissimi nostri filii regis <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/237"
                            >Henrici</persName> precibus pietatis aures accomodantes per presentis
                        precepti stabile firmamentum sancte <placeName ref="#places/106"
                            >Vercellensi</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Mother_churches">ecclesie</rs>
                        <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">confirmamus</rs> omnia bona quiete tenenda
                        ac pacifice imperpetuum fruenda, que <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/81"
                            key="#Mother_churches">sancto Eusebio</orgName> olim collata sunt a
                        nostris predecessoribus regibus vel imperatoribus seu quibuscunque
                        fidelibus. Set ut mentes fidelium plenius gaudeant et predones cautius se
                        custodiant, <geogName ref="#estates/131"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus #Profits_of_justice #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            >Vercellensem</geogName>
                        <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs> et <geogName ref="#estates/132"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus #Profits_of_justice #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            >sancte Agathe </geogName>cum <rs key="#Districtio">districto</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Teloneum">teloneo</rs> ac universa publica functione vel
                        exactione aut redhibitione confirmamus <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/81"
                            key="#Mother_churches">Eusebiane ecclesie</orgName>; <placeName
                            ref="#places/50"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Bugellam</placeName> insuper cum omni sua integritate, id est
                            <placeName ref="#places/591"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Vernade</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/212"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Clauaza</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/457"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Bedolium</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/206"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Galianicum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/208"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Ponderanam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/518"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Mulinariam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/210"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Andurnum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/211"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cisidulam</placeName> curticellam in monte, <placeName ref="#places/3"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Carisianam</placeName> cum omni sua integritate, <placeName
                            ref="#places/51"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sestegnum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/96"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rouasindam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/517"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montem Victimali</placeName>, <placeName>Pedrorium</placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> quoque <geogName ref="#estates/274"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Vercellensis civitatis</geogName> cum omnibus ad eam pertinentibus,
                        curticellam in <placeName ref="#places/227"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Audenico</placeName>, curtem <geogName ref="#estates/129"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName>Canauam</placeName></geogName>, curtem
                            <geogName>Caualli</geogName>, <rs key="#Monasteries">abbatiam</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/107"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >sancti Michaelis de Laucedio</orgName>, <placeName ref="#places/99"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Firminianam</placeName>; curtem regiam quam <geogName
                            ref="#estates/273"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName>Orcum</placeName></geogName> nominant cum tota <rs
                            key="#Forests">silva</rs> walda et <placeName ref="#places/49"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Fulgitio</placeName> et cum omnibus cortibus et villis, cum valle
                            <placeName ref="#places/103"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cliui</placeName>; <rs key="#Bridges/pontoons">pontem</rs> eciam
                        Notingum, quem <persName ref="#people/109"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Bishops"
                            >Notingus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> eiusdem Vercellensis ecclesie mirabiliter
                        super eum equitando legaliter recepit; <placeName ref="#places/100"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Languscum</placeName>, curtem de <geogName ref="#estates/98"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName>Aucimiano</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus suis
                        pertinentiis, <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Fisheries #Fluvial_transport #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >aquam</rs> de Scicida, aquam de Saruo, aquam de Eleuo cum utrisque
                        ripis a loco ubi nascuntur usque in Padum, aquam Padi cum utrisque ripis a
                            <placeName>Lionna</placeName> usque <rs key="#Plebs">plebem</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/229">Martori</orgName>, aquam de Duria cum
                        utrisque ripis a Petra grossa usque in Padum, <placeName ref="#places/221"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cousade</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/592">Martasca</placeName>,
                            <placeName ref="#places/213"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Candeli</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/215"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Treuere</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/214"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cleuoli</placeName>, Sulzam cum silva <geogName ref="#estates/184"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Forests"
                            >Salsa</geogName>, <rs key="#Castle">castellum</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/450"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Quirini</placeName>, curtem <geogName ref="#estates/128"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName>Torcelli</placeName></geogName> -- hec omnia sancta
                        Vercellensis ecclesia proprio iure habeat in eternum cum omnibus publicis
                        districtis <rs key="#Markets">mercatis</rs> teloneis <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscationibus</rs> venationibus <rs key="#Ports">portibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> montibus et vallibus alpibus edificiis
                        mancipiis utriusque sexus agris vineis cappellis pratis <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">pascuis</rs> silvis aquis aquarum decursibus
                        cultis et incultis. Et insuper speciali edicto sancimus, ut in omnibus et
                        per omnia supra nominatis locis nullus mortalium mercatum presumat
                        instituere aut districtum vel teloneum aut <rs key="#Fodrum">fodrum</rs> seu
                        aliquam publicam functionem ac redhibitionem exigere neque piscationem aut
                        venationem exercere, nisi ad profectum vel ad proprium ius ipsius ecclesie.
                        Quicunque ergo huic nostre confirmationi contraierit, nostre maiestatis reus
                        erit, insuper mille libras auri se compositurum noverit, medietatem
                        imperiali <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere</rs> et medietatem ecclesie, cui
                        molestiam intulerit. Quod ut firmius habeatur et diligentius ab omnibus
                        observetur, hoc preceptum ex nostra iussione factum nostris manibus subtus
                        firmavimus ac sigilli nostri impressione inferius insigniri iussimus et
                            <persName ref="#people/288" key="#Bishops">Arderico</persName> nostro
                        fidelissimo deo dispensante a nobis ordinato sancti Eusebii vicario ad
                        perpetuam pacem conservandam contulimus. Signum domini <persName
                            ref="#people/261" key="#Emperor/king">Chuonradi</persName> (M. IMP.)
                        serenissimi atque invictissimi imperatoris augusti. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
